            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">When Yin went from Xia to Bo, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">in the middle of the night he came in the presence of Tang. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">Tang said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">"Come, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">you have an auspicious intent." </seg>
            </p>

            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">Yin said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">"Majesty, since I arrived (from Xia) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">ten days have passed. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">(Before leaving) I inspected Xia </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">the many (officials) are not stabble and harmonious, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">as for the ruler, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">his intent is bad (lacking). </seg>
            </p>

            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">He bestows favor on the two jades [his two favourite wives], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">but does not worry (care) about his people. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">The people really (murmuring) say: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">"We will perish together!" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">He increasingly damages virtue </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">is violent in his actions </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">and lawless. </seg>
            </p>

            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">(Therefore) the ruler of Xia received omens, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">they were both in the west and in the east, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">appearing manifest in Heaven. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">His people all said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">"It will quickly bringing disaster upon us (=our ruler is ruining our own country) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">They all said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">"Why now is the omen in the east not (yet) manifest? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">Now how should we do?" </seg>
            </p>

            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">Tang said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">"What you told me you [=Yin] saw (?) in Xia, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">is it really (?) like this?" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">Yin said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">"It is like this." </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">Tang made an oath of covenant with Yin, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">and he then appeased (the people), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">making a great rite against drought. </seg>
            </p>

            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">Tang went on a punitive expedition, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">against those who didn't submit; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">Zhi (=Yin)'s counsels and virtue were not lacking. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">From the west he attacked the Western City (capital of Xia), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">subduing Xia. </seg>
            </p>

            <p>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">Xia counted its people </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">making them enter into the Shui river (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">saying: "Fight!" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en">The primordial ruler (=Tang) said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0089_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en">"Do not let even one survive!" </seg>
            </p>

         </div>
